Corporation FAQs










 













Corporation FAQs





Corporations FAQ
Find answers to questions about what corporations are, how they work, and whether or not you should incorporate.




What happens if we forget to hold an annual meeting?
My husband and I just formed a Texas corporation this year, of which we are the only shareholders and directors. We forgot that we had, in our bylaws, set the annual meeting for the first Monday in December, which is already past. What is the best way to handle this now?




How do I quit being an S corporation officer?
I'm an officer of an S corporation, but I'd like to get out of this position and terminate my association with the corporation. If I do so, will I remain responsible for any corporate liabilities? Do I need a lawyer?




How do I start a pension plan for my C corporation?
I have just started a company, a C corporation. I want to start a pension plan by contributing the maximum possible amount into a money purchase plan and managing the assets (stocks) myself. Can I just open a brokerage account, call it XYZ Pension Fund, and do it?




Am I liable for co-shareholders' decisions in an S corporation?
My partner and I have formed an S corporation, with him as secretary and me as president. The landlord and my partner worked out the rent and it increased significantly with changes that my partner suggested to the builder. Now the rent will be too expensive for the business to succeed, in my opinion. The landlord has sent me a five-year lease to sign and it has a clause for us to sign to personally indemnify and guarantee all money. I do not intend to sign it. Can I be held personally responsible for the money that the landlord has paid the builder for this building -- or anything else?




How do I serve a corporation that has no agent?
I'm planning on filing a lawsuit against an out-of-state corporation that owns retail locations in California. I was instructed to serve its agent for service, but the company does not have one. How can I properly serve the business -- and is it legal for it to continue doing business in California without having an agent?




Can our nonprofit get in trouble for failing to file tax returns?
We live in a townhouse run by a nonprofit association.  The CC&Rs say that  the association is a nonprofit organization. Do we need to file taxes yearly? Our ex-treasurer did not file for the past two years. I think we might be in trouble. Are we?




Can my corporate directors be H-1B visa holders?
In California (the home state of the questioner), the law places no restrictions on who may be directors.




I want to sell but the other shareholder doesn't. Who wins?
A friend and I formed a corporation together, and we share ownership equally. The business is in financial trouble now, and I would like to sell it and make at least something out of it before it is too late. My partner says she cannot afford to buy me out and refuses to sell. What should I do?




Should my very small business incorporate in Delaware?
I have heard that Delaware has the most business-friendly corporation laws. Would I save money or gain other benefits if I incorporated my new two-owner business in Delaware, or is it better to do so in my own state?

















